'''乐舞语'''是一种已灭亡的曾在中国[[云南省|云南省]][[景东彝族自治县|景东彝族自治县]]使用的[[彝语支|彝语支]]语言。乐舞人被中国政府划为[[瑶族|瑶族]]。

==人口结构学==
据''景东县年鉴''(1994:519)，瑶族在1990年有3,889人，主要生活在太忠乡岔箐<ref name="ynszxc">{{cite web|url=http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=217095|website=ynszxc.gov.cn|title=景东彝族自治县太忠乡岔箐村委会|access-date=2017-12-30|archive-date=2013-12-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131230232920/http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=217095|dead-url=no}}</ref>和大松树<ref name="ynszxc2">{{cite web|url=http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=217070|website=ynszxc.gov.cn|title=景东彝族自治县太忠乡大松树村委会|access-date=2017-12-30|archive-date=2013-12-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131230235247/http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=217070|dead-url=no}}</ref>等地。瑶语使用者被称为乐舞瑶族，分布在岔箐乡普牙村(''景东县民族志'' 2012:144)。<ref name="ynszxc3">{{cite web|url=http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=217633|website=ynszxc.gov.cn|title=景东彝族自治县太忠乡岔箐村委会上普牙|access-date=2017-12-30|archive-date=2018-06-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612140228/http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=217633|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="ynszxc4">{{cite web|url=http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=217632|website=ynszxc.gov.cn|title=景东彝族自治县太忠乡岔箐村委会中普牙|access-date=2017-12-30|archive-date=2018-06-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612145403/http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=217632|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="ynszxc5">{{cite web|url=http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=217630|website=ynszxc.gov.cn|title=景东彝族自治县太忠乡岔箐村委会下普牙|access-date=2017-12-30|archive-date=2018-06-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612143539/http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=217630|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==分类==
乐舞语可能和[[云南省|云南省]][[新平彝族傣族自治县|新平彝族傣族自治县]]的[[拉邬语|拉邬语]]有亲缘关系，但因为资料短缺其分类地位仍不明确。<ref>Hsiu, Andrew. 2017. ''[https://zenodo.org/record/1249178/files/Lawu_languages.pdf The Lawu languages: footprints along the Red River valley corridor] {{Wayback|url=https://zenodo.org/record/1249178/files/Lawu_languages.pdf |date=20180518200659 }}''.</ref>

